      "date": "2011-05-29 08:09:15.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\nThe use of OBD_ALLOC_LARGE seems fine, but the real question is whether the -ENOMEM is in the Lustre code at all. If OBD_ALLOC() fails it should print an error message on the console, which wasn't reported here.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "c4dcd8e918ff096c6dcdcaad08be752513493851",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 147,
        "name": "Maloo",
        "email": "maloo@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "maloo",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2011-05-29 11:33:59.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Fails\n\nTests received by maloo, run on CentOS release 5.6/x86_64: (https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/ff896e7e-89e6-11e0-b4df-52540025f9af).  Ran 16 tests.  1 tests failed: sanity-benchmark.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
